President Obama released a statement expressing his condolences on the passing of Howard Baker. He praised Baker's ability to broker compromise and his unofficial role as the "Great Conciliator" that earned him admiration across party lines and generations. Obama highlighted Baker's accomplishments as Senate Majority Leader, White House Chief of Staff, and Ambassador, as well as his dedication to serving the people of Tennessee. The President extended his thoughts and prayers to Baker's wife Nancy and the entire Baker family.